The first speaker heard was Mr. Sheppard, of Wyoming. abstract: The snow-storm which began at 10:30 o'clock Sunday night lasted until the same hour yesterday forenoon. Then it gave way to a five-hour rainstorm, which was just heavy enough to turn the snow into the sloppiest kind of slush, and thus make traveling exceedingly unpleasant, as well as difficult. About three inches of snow and one-fifth of an inch of rain fell during the storm.
